data.text: @BobLWebDesign Yeah, obviously they are better! I'm just a big hypochondriac 😅

@natension I got mine on a Friday morning and was fine the rest of the day. I was then wiped out most of Saturday with tiredness and aches but otherwise good. By about 6pm I felt good again, you'll be fine
@natension You'll probably have some. They're usually mild. They're better than getting COVID. You got this!

@MattVisiwig @_joshuafonseca Obviously! Just hypochondring around 😅
I think that I have a heart attack or stroke at least twice a month 😅

@_joshuafonseca Yeah, that helps a bit 😅 both my parents have at least one shot and had no side effects at all, but they had a different vaccine than I got. The good thing is, my girlfriend got the vaccine today as well 😅

@natension @_joshuafonseca You're not the first to get the vaccine, if you feel any side effects, they're short-lived.

Easily 1000x better than the side-effects of no-one getting vaccinated.

@natension @_joshuafonseca Ooh, I get that feeling. I was also looking for signals in my body after my first shot.

Didn't get sick, only the usual vaccination-soreness at the entry-point so to say. 😉
@_joshuafonseca Anxious about side effects 😅 I'm a big hypochondriac 😂
